[See http://www.albanydailystar.com/health/15-year-old-boy-died-from-ebola-miami-gardens-tech-week-11590.html for more information on these latest cases.

Because of the persistence of virus in humans as well as wildlife, it may not be possible to completely eliminate Ebola from the environment in West Africa, at least in the near term. If it is kept under control, eventually it may be eliminated locally. If clinics follow appropriate biosafety protocols to prevent spread of the virus, with use of personal protective equipment if available, Ebola should be able to be kept to a minimum of cases. Vaccination also will help control spread. - Mod.LK]

